cyPM.name: cyPM
cyPM.contactinfo: postal : Cyclades Corporation 3541 Gateway Boulevard Fremont, CA 94538, USA e-mail : Technical Support support@cyclades.com
cyPM.description: This module defines objects of the Proxy for PM

cyNumberOfPM.name: cyNumberOfPM
cyNumberOfPM.description: The total number of PM's connected on the unit

cyPMTable.name: cyPMTable
cyPMTable.description: Allows to read information about each connected PM

cyPMSerialPortNumber.name: cyPMSerialPortNumber
cyPMSerialPortNumber.description: The number of the serial port when the PM is connected.

cyPMNumberUnits.name: cyPMNumberUnits
cyPMNumberUnits.description: Total number of PM unists that are accessed by this serial port.

cyPMVersion.name: cyPMVersion
cyPMVersion.description: The software version of the PM.

cyPMCommand.name: cyPMCommand
cyPMCommand.description: A character string for the user to send commands to PM. He can use it to does the save command. Or to list the outlets that need to be turned off, or turned on , or cycled or locked or unlocked as a group. The command is the first word and is followed by a space and the outlet list (otulets commands). Valid commands are 'on', 'off', 'cycle', 'lock', 'unlock', 'save'.

cyPMUnitTable.name: cyPMUnitTable
cyPMUnitTable.description: Allow operations on specific PM unit connected

cyPMUnitNumber.name: cyPMUnitNumber
cyPMUnitNumber.description: The number of the PM unit in the daisy-chained mode.

cyPMUnitVersion.name: cyPMUnitVersion
cyPMUnitVersion.description: The software version of this PM unit.

cyPMUnitOutlets.name: cyPMUnitOutlets
cyPMUnitOutlets.description: Number of outlets of this PM unit.

cyPMUnitFirstOutlet.name: cyPMUnitFirstOutlet
cyPMUnitFirstOutlet.description: Number of the first outlet of this PM unit.

cyPMUnitCurrent.name: cyPMUnitCurrent
cyPMUnitCurrent.description: Current of this PM unit in AMP. The value of this object is the actual current in AMP * 10. You need to translate the readed value (Ex. : value is 5, the current is 0.5 AMP.)

cyPMUnitMaxCurrent.name: cyPMUnitMaxCurrent
cyPMUnitMaxCurrent.description: Maximum current of this PM unit in AMP. The value of this object is the maximum current in AMP * 10. You need to translate the readed value (Ex. : value is 5, the maximum current is 0.5 AMP.)

cyPMUnitTemperature.name: cyPMUnitTemperature
cyPMUnitTemperature.description: Temperature of this PM unit in Celsius degrees. The value of this object is the actual temperature in degrees C * 10. You need to translate the readed value (Ex. : value is 240, the temperature is 24 Celsius.) If the temperature measurement is not installed this value will be 0. Valid values are 5 to 999 ( 0.5 to 99.9 Celsius).

cyPMUnitMaxTemperature.name: cyPMUnitMaxTemperature
cyPMUnitMaxTemperature.description: Maximum temperature value of this PM unit in Celsius degrees. The value of this object is the maximum temperature in degrees C * 10. You need to translate the readed value(Ex. : value is 240, the maximum temperature is 24 Celsius). If the temperature measurement is not installed this value will be 0. Valid values are 5 to 999 ( 0.5 to 99.9 Celsius).

cyOutletNumber.name: cyOutletNumber
cyOutletNumber.description: The outlet number on the PM. Zero is ALL outlets.

cyOutletName.name: cyOutletName
cyOutletName.description: The name given to a particular outlet Maximum size is 8 characters.

cyOutletServer.name: cyOutletServer
cyOutletServer.description: Alias of the Server connected to this outlet .

cyOutletPower.name: cyOutletPower
cyOutletPower.description: Getting this object will return the power state of the outlet. Valid return states are UNKNOW, OFF and ON. Setting this object will change the power state of the outlet.

cyOutletLock.name: cyOutletLock
cyOutletLock.description: Getting this object will return the lock state of the outlet. Setting this object will change the lock state of the outlet.

cyOutletPUInterval.name: cyOutletPUInterval
cyOutletPUInterval.description: The power unit interval of this outlet in seconds. The value of this object is the actual interval in seconds * 10. You need to translate the readed value (Ex. : value is 5, the interval is 0.5 seconds.)
